        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "mY-nUm
(MY-num)")))
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "By calling"
          (code
            "quote")
          "or using the reader-macro"
          (code
            "'")
          ", you can return the names of the symbols, rather than evaluating and returning the values of the symbols.")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "'my-num ; => MY-NUM"))))
      (article :class "almighty-section"
        (h3 :id "introducing-global-variables" :class "almighty-section-title"
          "Introducing Global Variables")
        (article :class "almighty-section"
          (h4 :id "variables-with-no-starting-value" :class "almighty-section-title"
            "Variables with no starting value")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "If you want to introduce a variable you have a few options.")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "Use"
            (code
              "defvar")
            "to introduce a global variable without a value.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defvar *a-variable-with-no-value*)")))
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "To change the value of a"
            (code
              "defvar")
            "variable, you need to call"
            (code
              "setf")
            "on the variable."))
        (article :class "almighty-section"
          (h4 :id "variables-whose-value-can-change" :class "almighty-section-title"
            "Variables whose value can change")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "Use"
            (code
              "defparameter")
            "to introduce a global variable with a starting value that can be modified.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defparameter *a-global-var* 'hello-world)")))
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "Global variables defined with"
            (code
              "defvar")
            "and"
            (code
              "defparameter")
            "are surrounded with"
            (code
              "*")
            "by convention."))
        (article :class "almighty-section"
          (h4 :id "variables-with-values-that-don-t-change" :class "almighty-section-title"
            "Variables with values that don't change")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "Use"
            (code
              "defconstant")
            "to introduce a global variable that has a value that can't be modified.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defconstant +pi+ 3.14)")))
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "Constant variable names are surrounded with"
            (code
              "+")
            "by convention."))
        (article :class "almighty-section"
          (h4 :id "modifying-the-value-of-a-variable" :class "almighty-section-title"
            "Modifying the value of a variable")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "You can also use"
            (code
              "setf")
            "to assign values to variables you've already introduced.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(setf *a-global-var* 'goodnight-world)")))
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "You have to use"
            (code
              "setf")
            "to modify the value of a"
            (code
              "defvar")
            "variable, but"
            (code
              "defparameter")
            "variable values can be modified with another call to"
            (code
              "defparameter")
            "with a new value for the variable.")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "Using"
            (code
              "setf")
            "on a variable that you haven't introduced yet will result in a warning.")))
      (article :class "almighty-section"
        (h3 :id "introducing-local-variables" :class "almighty-section-title"
          "Introducing Local Variables")
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "Use"
          (code
            "let")
          "to introduce a local variable. The variable will only exist or contain the set value inside the"
          (code
            "let")
          "form.")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "(let ((lucky-num 7))
  lucky-num)
 ; => 7 (3 bits, #x7, #o7, #b111)")))
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "You can also reassign a global variable temporarily.")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "(defparameter *var* 'outside)
*var*                   ; => OUTSIDE
(let ((*var* 'inside))   ; *var* is reassigned a new value.
  *var*)                ; => INSIDE
*var*                   ; => OUTSIDE")))
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "When variables have different values depending on their context, it's called"
          (code
            "lexical scoping")
          ". Scoping variables is critical to avoiding bugs.")
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "There are several other ways to introduce locally-scoped variables. One of them is inside"
          (code
            "defun")
          "definitions."))
      (article :class "almighty-section"
        (h3 :id "more-than-just-variables" :class "almighty-section-title"
          "More than just variables")
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "While variables are an important kind of symbol, they aren't the only kind of symbol. Function names, package names, class names, etc. are all symbols. Symbols themselves are a data structure and can hold more than one piece of information.")))
    (article :class "almighty-section"
      (h2 :id "functions" :class "almighty-section-title"
        "FUNCTIONS")
      (article :class "almighty-section"
        (h3 :id "defining-named-functions" :class "almighty-section-title"
          "Defining Named Functions")
        (article :class "almighty-section"
          (h4 :id "globally" :class "almighty-section-title"
            "Globally")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "You can define functions with"
            (code
              "defun")
            ":")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun sum (x y) ; x and y are now locally-scoped variables
  (+ x y))")))
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "All functions defined with"
            (code
              "defun")
            "are global in scope.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun categorize-food (food)
  (defun compile-food-ingredients (food) ...) ; This is global, don't do it!
  ...)"))))
        (article :class "almighty-section"
          (h4 :id "locally" :class "almighty-section-title"
            "Locally")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "To define locally-scoped named functions, use"
            (code
              "flet")
            "or"
            (code
              "labels")
            ":")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun squirt-then-double (x)
  (flet ((squirt (y)                        ; Locally-scoped function named \"squirt\".
           (* y y)))
    (* 2 (squirt x))))

(defun squirt-then-double-with-let (x)
  (flet ((squirt (y)
           (* y y)))
    (let ((squirted (squirt x)))            ; Nesting let, flet, etc. is perfectly crumulent.
      (* 2 squirted))))

(defun squirt-then-double-with-labels (x)
  (labels ((squirt (y)                      ; labels is the equivalent of let* for functions
             (* y y))
           (double ()
             (* 2 (squirt x))))
    (double x)))")))))
      (article :class "almighty-section"
        (h3 :id "lambda-list" :class "almighty-section-title"
          "Lambda List")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "(defun a-fun (a b c))")))
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "The second parameter to"
          (code
            "defun")
          "is called a"
          (code
            "lambda list")
          ". Parameters for the function being defined are specified inside the lambda list."))
      (article :class "almighty-section"
        (h3 :id "parameters" :class "almighty-section-title"
          "Parameters")
        (article :class "almighty-section"
          (h4 :id "required" :class "almighty-section-title"
            "required")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "Parameters defined without any other options are required.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun my-fun (this-is-required))"))))
        (article :class "almighty-section"
          (h4 :id "optional" :class "almighty-section-title"
            "=&optional=")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "You can define different types of parameters with"
            (code
              "lambda list keywords")
            ".")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "Define optional parameters with the"
            (code
              "&optional")
            "lambda list keyword.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun fun-with-optional (a &optional b)
  (format t \"The values passed: ~a and ~a.~&\" a b))

(fun-with-optional 5) ; => The values passed: 5 and NIL.")))
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "The default value for optional arguments not passed is"
            (code
              "nil")
            ". You can set the default value.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun fun-with-optional (a &optional (b 10))
  (format t \"The values passed: ~a and ~a.~&\" a b))

(fun-with-optional 5) ; => The values passed: 5 and 10.")))
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "You can create a predicate that will return whether the value was supplied or the default is being used.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun fun-with-optional (a &optional (b 10 b-supplied-p))
  (if b-supplied-p
      (format t \"The values passed: ~a and ~a (passed by user).~&\" a b)
      (format t \"The values passed: ~a and ~a (default).~&\" a b)))

(fun-with-optional 5) ; => The values passed: 5 and 10 (default).
(fun-with-optional 5 10) ; => The values passed: 5 and 10 (passed by user).")))
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "All parameters following the"
            (code
              "&optional")
            "lambda list keyword will be optional. This is true of all lambda list keywords.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun fun-with-lots-of-options (&optional (a 1) (b 2) (c 3))
  (+ a b c))
(fun-with-lots-of-options)              ; => 6
(fun-with-lots-of-options 2)            ; => 7
(fun-with-lots-of-options 5 5 5)        ; => 15"))))
        (article :class "almighty-section"
          (h4 :id "key" :class "almighty-section-title"
            "=&key=")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "Define named parameters using"
            (code
              "&key")
            ".")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun fun-with-keys (&key a b c)
  (+ a b c))
(fun-with-keys :a 1 :b 2 :c 3)          ; => 6")))
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "As with"
            (code
              "&optional")
            ", you can specify default values.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun fun-with-keys (&key (a 1) (b 2) (c 3))
  (+ a b c))
(fun-with-keys)                         ; => 6
(fun-with-keys :c 5 :b 7 :a 3)          ; => 15")))
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            (code
              "-supplied-p")
            "predicates can also be specified.")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun fun-with-keys (&key (a 1 a-supplied-p) (b 2 b-supplied-p) (c 3 c-supplied-p))
  (format t \"~a (~a) + ~a (~a) + ~a (~a) = ~a~&\" a a-supplied-p b b-supplied-p c c-supplied-p (+ a b c)))
(fun-with-keys)
                                        ; 1 (NIL) + 2 (NIL) + 3 (NIL) = 6
                                        ;  => NIL
(fun-with-keys :c 5 :b 7 :a 3)
                                        ; 3 (T) + 7 (T) + 5 (T) = 15
                                        ;  => NIL"))))
        (article :class "almighty-section"
          (h4 :id "rest" :class "almighty-section-title"
            "=&rest=")
          (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
            "Collect arbitrary arguments into a list with"
            (code
              "&rest")
            ".")
          (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
            (pre
              (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                "(defun fun-with-rest (&rest args)
  (loop for arg in args
        do (print arg)))
(fun-with-rest 'a)                      ; A  => NIL
(fun-with-rest 'a 'b 5 \"rest a while\")
                                        ; A
                                        ; B
                                        ; 5
                                        ; \"rest a while\"  => NIL

(defun add (&rest args)
