(do-a-bunch-of-stuff)")))
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "There are cases, however, when you might want to do an early return, especially when looping. You can do that with"
          (code
            "return")
          "."))
      (article :class "almighty-section"
        (h3 :id "returning-multiple-values" :class "almighty-section-title"
          "Returning Multiple Values")
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "It's possible to return multiple values using the"
          (code
            "values")
          "function.")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "(defun return-a-bunch-of-stuff ()
  (values
   (+ 2 7)
