      (article :class "almighty-section"
        (h3 :id "breaking-lists-into-multiple-values" :class "almighty-section-title"
          "Breaking Lists Into Multiple Values")
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "Sometimes you might want to take a list and break it into pieces--called destructuring. For that, there's"
          (code
            "destructuring-bind")
          ".")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "(destructuring-bind (a b c)
    (list 1 2 3)
  (format t \"~a * ~a * ~a = ~a\" a b c (* a b c)))
                                        ; 1 * 2 * 3 = 6 => NIL")))
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "This destructuring can be done on arbitrarily deep trees of cons cells.")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "(defparameter *deep-tree* `(defun function-name (a lambda-list)
                            (let ((b :some-value))
                              b)))

(destructuring-bind (the-defun the-function-name (the-a the-lambda-list)
                     (the-let ((the-b the-value-bound-to-b))
                      the-b-at-the-end))
    *deep-tree*
  the-value-bound-to-b)
