      (article :class "almighty-section"
        (h3 :id "lists-as-trees" :class "almighty-section-title"
          "Lists as Trees")
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "Lists are a very simple data structure capable of making other data structures. Consider the linked list of cons cells above:")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "(cons 'defun (cons 'sum (cons (cons 'x
                                     (cons 'y nil))
                               (cons
                                (cons '+
                                      (cons 'x (cons 'y nil)))
                                nil))))")))
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "While it is simply a linked list of cons cells, it's useful to think of it another way: a tree. Each cons cell has two parts: a car and a cdr. The car holds a leaf in the tree, whereas the cdr holds either another branch (in the common case) or another leaf. When working with lists as a tree, you can use"
          (code
            "car")
          "and"
          (code
            "cdr")
          "to access those two positions.")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "(setq my-tree (cons 'defun (cons 'sum (cons (cons 'x
                                     (cons 'y nil))
                               (cons
                                (cons '+
                                      (cons 'x (cons 'y nil)))
                                nil)))))

(car my-tree) ; => DEFUN
(cdr my-tree) ; => (SUM (X Y) (+ X Y))")))
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "You can copy a tree:")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "(copy-tree my-tree)")))
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "You can substitute leaves in the tree:")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              ";; Take all instances of y in the tree and replace them with z
(subst 'z 'y my-tree)

;; Substitute multiple leaves in a tree
(sublis '((sum . subtract) (+ . -)) my-tree)"))))
      (article :class "almighty-section"
        (h3 :id "lists-as-tables" :class "almighty-section-title"
          "Lists as Tables")
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          (code
            "sublis")
          "takes a special type of list for its first argument: an association list, otherwise known as an alist or table. A table is a list with nested dotted lists--lists that have a non-nil leaf in the cdr position.")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
          (pre
            (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
              "(setf en-to-ja-table '((one . ichi)
                       (two . ni)
                       (three . san)
                       (four . yon)
                       (five . go)))")))
        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
          "With tables, the car is a key and the cdr is a value. You can search a table by either key or value.")
        (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
