                                              (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                (h2 :id "window-navigation-management" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                  "WINDOW NAVIGATION & MANAGEMENT")
                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                  (h3 :id "getting-familiar-with-windows" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                    "Getting Familiar With Windows")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "In Emacs, a \"frame\" is what most people would call a window: an operating system-level defined space to display the contents of an application.")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "Emacs uses the word \"window\" differently from how operating systems do. Emacs windows are separate places where buffers can be displayed. Buffers, of course, show either file contents or things like the Lisp REPL. A frame can be subdivided into many windows, each displaying a single buffer at a time.")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "Opening, closing, and navigating between windows are essential skills for using Emacs. Now that you know the basics of Lisp, it's time to become more familiar with windows."))
                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                  (h3 :id "splitting-closing-windows" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                    "Splitting & Closing Windows")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "You can split a window vertically or horizontally (creating another window).")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "To split vertically, type"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-x 2")
                                                    "or"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC w s")
                                                    ".
To split horizontally, type"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-x 3")
                                                    "or"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC w v")
                                                    ".")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "You can delete a window with"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-x 0")
                                                    "or"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC w d")
                                                    ", or you can close all"
                                                    (i
                                                      "except")
                                                    "the currently selected window with"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-x 1")
                                                    "or"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-w C-o")
                                                    "."))
                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                  (h3 :id "moving-between-windows" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                    "Moving Between Windows")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "While you can use the mouse to move the cursor around, eventually you'll want to learn to use keybindings instead. Trust me, it's nice.")
                                                  (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                    (h4 :id "ace-window" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                      "Ace window")
                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                      "You can use the"
                                                      (code
                                                        "ace-window")
                                                      "packages' functionality to switch windows. Type"
                                                      (code
                                                        "C-x o")
                                                      "or"
                                                      (code
                                                        "C-w C-w")
                                                      "to run"
                                                      (code
                                                        "ace-window")
                                                      ". If there are only two windows open, then it will move the cursor to the one that isn't currently active. If however, you have three or more windows open,"
                                                      (code
                                                        "ace-window")
                                                      "will display letters at the top left of each buffer. Typing the letter displayed in a window will move the cursor to that window.")
                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                      "This method is my preferred method of switching windows because it works regardless of what Evil state or Emacs major mode I'm in. It's also more direct. However, it does require some getting used to. As a beginner, you can't predict what letter you can use to switch to a window. Thus, in the beginning this method will often be slower then the next method I'll introduce to you."))
                                                  (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                    (h4 :id "evil-window" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                      "Evil window")
                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                      "The next method uses"
                                                      (code
                                                        "evil-window")
                                                      "keybindings. With"
                                                      (code
                                                        "evil")
                                                      "navigation, in Normal State, you navigate the cursor one line up and down with"
                                                      (code
                                                        "j")
                                                      "and"
                                                      (code
                                                        "k")
                                                      ", and one character left and right with"
                                                      (code
                                                        "h")
                                                      "and"
                                                      (code
                                                        "l")
                                                      ".")
                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                      "Using this familiar navigation method, you switch windows like this:")
                                                    (ul :class "org-ul"
                                                      (li
                                                        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                          (code
                                                            "SPC w l")
                                                          "or"
                                                          (code
                                                            "C-w l")
                                                          "("
                                                          (code
                                                            "evil-window-right")
                                                          "), move the cursor one window to the right."))
                                                      (li
                                                        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                          (code
                                                            "SPC w h")
                                                          "or"
                                                          (code
                                                            "C-w h")
                                                          "("
                                                          (code
                                                            "evil-window-left")
                                                          "), move the cursor one window to the left."))
                                                      (li
                                                        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                          (code
                                                            "SPC w j")
                                                          "or"
                                                          (code
                                                            "C-w j")
                                                          "("
                                                          (code
                                                            "evil-window-down")
                                                          "), move the cursor one window down."))
                                                      (li
                                                        (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                          (code
                                                            "SPC w k")
                                                          "or"
                                                          (code
                                                            "C-w k")
                                                          "("
                                                          (code
                                                            "evil-window-down")
                                                          "), move the cursor one window up.")))
                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                      "It's simple and effective. Even with experience, you may prefer it over using"
                                                      (code
                                                        "ace-window")
                                                      ". However, as I said above, all of these shortcuts require you to be in Evil Normal State ("
                                                      (code
                                                        "C-w")
                                                      "in Insert State is mapped to"
                                                      (code
                                                        "evil-delete-backward-word")
                                                      ").")))
                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                  (h3 :id "moving-window-positions" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                    "Moving Window Positions")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "The above commands move the"
                                                    (i
                                                      "cursor")
                                                    "from one window to another. It's also possible to move a window from one position to another.")
                                                  (ul :class "org-ul"
                                                    (li
                                                      (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                        (code
                                                          "SPC w L")
                                                        "or"
                                                        (code
                                                          "C-w L")
                                                        "("
                                                        (code
                                                          "+evil/window-move-right")
                                                        ")"))
                                                    (li
                                                      (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                        (code
                                                          "SPC w H")
                                                        "or"
                                                        (code
                                                          "C-w H")
                                                        "("
                                                        (code
                                                          "+evil/window-move-left")
                                                        ")"))
                                                    (li
                                                      (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                        (code
                                                          "SPC w J")
                                                        "or"
                                                        (code
                                                          "C-w J")
                                                        "("
                                                        (code
                                                          "+evil/window-move-down")
                                                        ")"))
                                                    (li
                                                      (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                        (code
                                                          "SPC w K")
                                                        "or"
                                                        (code
                                                          "C-w K")
                                                        "("
                                                        (code
                                                          "+evil/window-move-up")
                                                        ")")))
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "Technically, it's more like you are switching"
                                                    (i
                                                      "buffers")
                                                    "between windows. What this means is that all windows maintain their current size; if you have one large window and one small window, if you run one of the above commands while the cursor is in the large window, the buffer in that window will appear in the smaller window"))
                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                  (h3 :id "resizing-windows" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                    "Resizing Windows")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "You probably won't find yourself resizing windows very often. Sometimes Emacs will do some weird resizing of windows for certain actions (keep an eye out when using"
                                                    (code
                                                      "sly-sticker-replay")
                                                    ", introduced in a later chapter) that you need to fix, you might want to dedicate a window to a certain buffer (such as the"
                                                    (code
                                                      "org-agenda")
                                                    "buffer, introduced in a later chapter) and keep it open, and thus want to make the window smaller. Or maybe you really need to micro-adjust everything.")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "You can use the mouse to resize windows (click and drag the border between windows). It's honestly not such a bad idea since it will likely be an infrequent activity. However, it's also possible to resize windows with keybindings.")
                                                  (ul :class "org-ul"
                                                    (li
                                                      (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                        (code
                                                          "C-x {")
                                                        "("
                                                        (code
                                                          "shrink-window-horizontally")
                                                        ") or"
                                                        (code
                                                          "SPC w >")
                                                        "or"
                                                        (code
                                                          "C-w >")
                                                        "("
                                                        (code
                                                          "evil-window-increase-width")
                                                        ")."))
                                                    (li
                                                      (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                        (code
                                                          "C-x }")
                                                        "("
                                                        (code
                                                          "enlarge-window-horizontally")
                                                        ") or"
                                                        (code
                                                          "SPC w <")
                                                        "or"
                                                        (code
                                                          "C-w <")
                                                        "("
                                                        (code
                                                          "evil-window-decrease-width")
                                                        ")."))
                                                    (li
                                                      (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                        (code
                                                          "SPC w +")
                                                        "or"
                                                        (code
                                                          "C-w +")
                                                        "("
                                                        (code
                                                          "evil-window-increase-height")
                                                        ")"))
                                                    (li
                                                      (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                        (code
                                                          "SPC w -")
                                                        "or"
                                                        (code
                                                          "C-w -")
                                                        "("
                                                        (code
                                                          "evil-window-decrease-height")
                                                        ")")))
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "Each of the above commands will resize by one line or character. If you are in"
                                                    (code
                                                      "evil")
                                                    "Normal State, you can type a number"
                                                    (code
                                                      "n")
                                                    "and then run the command"
                                                    (code
                                                      "n")
                                                    "times. In Normal State, typing"
                                                    (code
                                                      "50 SPC w >")
                                                    "will increase the window width by 50 characters.")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "You can also make one window larger than all your other windows using"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-w o")
                                                    "or"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC w o")
                                                    "("
                                                    (code
                                                      "doom/window-enlargen")
                                                    ").")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "You can make all windows equal in size with"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC w =")
                                                    "or"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-w =")
                                                    "("
                                                    (code
                                                      "balance-windows")
                                                    ")."))
                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                  (h3 :id "undoing-changes" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                    "Undoing Changes")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "Undoing any change is simple:"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-w u")
                                                    "or"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC w u")
                                                    "("
                                                    (code
                                                      "winner-undo")
                                                    ").")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "This is useful not only for typos (for example, maybe you accidentally typed"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-x C-x a")
                                                    "and accidently closed all but one window) or for strange changes made by Emacs (sometimes closing a minibuffer drastically resizes other windows for no known reason), but also for intentional changes. For example, the above"
                                                    (code
                                                      "doom/window-enlargen")
                                                    "command drastically resizes all windows. You can undo that change with"
                                                    (code
                                                      "winner-undo")
                                                    ".")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    (code
                                                      "winner-undo")
                                                    "no only undoes window resizes, but any changes to windows. If you accidentally closed a window, you can undo with"
                                                    (code
                                                      "winner-undo")
                                                    ". If you move a window, you can undo the move. It's perhaps one of the most essential commands for beginners who are most likely to make mistakes or be faced with strange changes in window arrangements they weren't expecting.")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "Of course, you can also run"
                                                    (code
                                                      "winner-redo")
                                                    "with"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-w C-r")
                                                    "or"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC w C-r")))
                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                  (h3 :id "more-about-windows" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                    "More About Windows")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "If you want to learn more about what's possible with windows, just type"
                                                    (code
                                                      "C-w")
                                                    "and look at the list of commands available in the minibuffer."))
