                                                        (code
                                                          "nth")
                                                        "workspace."))))
                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                  (h3 :id "saving-loading-project-workspaces" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                    "Saving & Loading Project Workspaces")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "Workspaces are not strictly speaking exclusive to projects. A workspace can be created independent of projects using"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC TAB n")
                                                    "("
                                                    (code
                                                      "+workspace/new")
                                                    "). If open some buffers, windows, etc. and then save the workspace with"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC TAB s")
                                                    ", you can close the workspace and reopen it with"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC TAB l")
                                                    ".")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "If you have a complex setup that you want to save, the ability to save the state of your workspace is a useful feature."))
                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                  (h3 :id "saving-project-files" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                    "Saving Project Files")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "Once you have a project/workspace open and start editing, you may find several files in your project haven't been saved. This is especially true in Common Lisp projects where you update them by compiling files or individual functions--with no need to save the application files in order to update them in memory.")
                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                    "To save all the files in your project, type"
                                                    (code
                                                      "SPC p s")
                                                    "("
                                                    (code
                                                      "projectile-save-project-buffers")
                                                    ")."))
                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                  (h3 :id "switching-project-buffers" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                    "Switching Project Buffers")
