                                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                                  (h2 :id "tracing" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                                    "TRACING")
                                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                    "Beyond simple navigation within the debugger is actual debugging methods and tools.")
                                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                    "Tracing is a debugging method that shows a form as it is called and then what it returns. Tracing is typically used for recursive functions.")
                                                                  (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                                    (h3 :id "sly-fancy-trace" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                                      "=sly-fancy-trace=")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "Let's say you have this function:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(defun factorial (n)
  \"Compute factorial using linear recursion.\"
  (if (= n 1)
      1
      (* n (factorial (- n 1)))))")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "You can run"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "trace")
                                                                      "on a function in Emacs like this:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(trace factorial)")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
