                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "You can also configure Sly to break when computation reaches the sticker using"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "sly-stickers-toggle-break-on-stickers")
                                                                      "via"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "SPC m s b")
                                                                      ". During computation, when a sticker is reached, the debugger will open with a message like this:")
                                                                    (pre :class "example" :id "orgc745868"
                                                                      "#<JUST BEFORE #<STICKER id=145 hit-count=1>>
   [Condition of type SLYNK-STICKERS::JUST-BEFORE-STICKER]")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "The sticker will also flash in the source code file window. Useful for when you have multiple stickers and need to know which one you're looking at.")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "If you choose the"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "CONTINUE")
                                                                      "restart (either via"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "c")
                                                                      "or"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "0")
                                                                      "or navigating to"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "[CONTINUE]")
                                                                      "and typing"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "Enter")
                                                                      ") or you use"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "sly-db-step")
                                                                      "via"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "s")
                                                                      "in the debugger window, you will see a message like this:")
                                                                    (pre :class "example" :id "org8a8dba9"
                                                                      "#<RIGHT-AFTER #<STICKER id=255 hit-count=2> (recorded #<RECORDING 1 values>)>
   [Condition of type SLYNK-STICKERS::RIGHT-AFTER-STICKER]")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "...and the return value of the form where the sticker is placed."))
                                                                  (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                                    (h3 :id "sly-stepper" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                                      "=sly-stepper=")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "If you are having trouble tracking down the exact location of your error, you can perform a comprehensive sweep using"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "sly-stepper")
                                                                      "with"
