                                                              (article :class "almighty-chapter"
                                                                (h1 :id "structured-editing" :class "almighty-chapter-title"
                                                                  "STRUCTURED EDITING")
                                                                (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                                  (h2 :id "restructuring-code-with-ease" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                                    "RESTRUCTURING CODE WITH EASE")
                                                                  (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                    "Writing Lisp code often involves moving forms around or wrapping forms in new forms. If you're using"
                                                                    (code
                                                                      "lispy-mode")
                                                                    "or"
                                                                    (code
                                                                      "lispyville-mode")
                                                                    "--both turned on with Doom's"
                                                                    (code
                                                                      "lispy")
                                                                    "config in the"
                                                                    (code
                                                                      "init.el")
                                                                    "file--you can more easily build out and modify Lisp code.")
                                                                  (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                                    (h3 :id "slurping-and-barfing" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                                      "Slurping and barfing")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "Slurping and barfing are terms for describing moving parentheses to either include or exclude forms from other forms. Let me show you what I mean.")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "In the tic-tac-toe project, we wrote code to find positions on the board to win or block the opponent's win. To begin, we wrote this:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(find-if #'(lambda (triplet) (= 20 (sum-triplet *test-board* triplet))) *triplets*)")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "This finds any triplet that sums to 20 on the board. But we then wanted to search the result of that"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "form to search for the empty space in the triplet.")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(find-if #'(lambda (element) (= (nth element board) 0))
         (find-if #'(lambda (triplet) (= 20 (sum-triplet *test-board* triplet))) *triplets*))")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "If you use structural editing, this can actually be difficult at first. You might naturally try to write the code like this:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(find-if #'(lambda (element) (= (nth element board) 0)))
(find-if #'(lambda (triplet) (= 20 (sum-triplet *test-board* triplet))) *triplets*)")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "And then, in order to wrap the bottom"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "form with the top"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "form, you might try to delete the final parenthesis of the top"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "and then move it to the end of the bottom"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "form:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(find-if #'(lambda (element) (= (nth element board) 0)) ; deleted paren
(find-if #'(lambda (triplet) (= 20 (sum-triplet *test-board* triplet))) *triplets*)) ; added paren")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "What actually happens, however, is that the entire top"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "form is deleted when you try to delete just the last parenthesis! This very confusing behavior is from"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "lispy-mode")
                                                                      ". It is designed to keep parentheses balanced at all times.")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "If you want to move only one parenthesis, then, what do you do?")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "One option would be to"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "kill")
                                                                      "the"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "form intended to become the inner form...")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(find-if #'(lambda (element) (= (nth element board) 0)) ; bottom form killed")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "and then paste it at the end of the outer"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "...")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(find-if #'(lambda (element) (= (nth element board) 0)) (find-if #'(lambda (triplet) (= 20 (sum-triplet *test-board* triplet))) *triplets*))")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "and then move the cursor to the beginning parenthesis of the inner"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "and press"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "ENTER")
                                                                      "to place it on a new line.")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(find-if #'(lambda (element) (= (nth element board) 0))
         (find-if #'(lambda (triplet) (= 20 (sum-triplet *test-board* triplet))) *triplets*))")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "This is okay, but there is an even easier method called"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "slurping")
                                                                      ".")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "Start with this code:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(find-if #'(lambda (element) (= (nth element board) 0)))
(find-if #'(lambda (triplet) (= 20 (sum-triplet *test-board* triplet))) *triplets*)")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "Place the cursor on the last parenthesis of the top form. While still in Evil Normal mode (not Insert mode), press"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        ">")
                                                                      "(the"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "lispyville-mode")
                                                                      "keybinding for"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "lispyville-slurp")
                                                                      "). The parenthesis will move to the"
                                                                      (b
                                                                        "end")
                                                                      "of the bottom"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "form, making it an inner nested form.")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "Slurping is especially useful for any time you need to \"build out\" from some code. Consider this:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(find-if #'(lambda (triple)
             (= (sum-triple *test-board* triple) target-sum))
         *triples*)")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "This is how we started building out the code for detecting squeezes. But then we realized that we needed to add more conditions. For a strategy to be a squeeze, the triplet need to sum to the target,"
                                                                      (b
                                                                        "and")
                                                                      "it needs to be diagonal as well as some other conditions. That means that we needed to wrap several predicate functions in an"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "and")
                                                                      "form.")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          ";; These need to be wrapped in an (and ...) form
(= (sum-triple board triple) target-sum)
(diagonal-p triple)")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "We can do that by first writing the"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "and")
                                                                      "form before the other two forms:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(and) (= (sum-triple board triple) target-sum)
(diagonal-p triple)")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "Put the Evil Normal-mode cursor on the end paren of the"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "and")
                                                                      "form, and then"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "slurp")
                                                                      "up the other two forms.")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(and (= (sum-triple board triple) target-sum)
     (diagonal-p triple))")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "Once we added the rest of the conditions, we wanted to then bind the return value of the"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "find-if")
                                                                      "form to a local variable using"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "let")
                                                                      ". The process looks like this:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          ";; Write the LET and variable we want in the LET.
;; let               Finished find-if
(let ((squeeze-p))) (find-if #'(lambda (triple)
             (and (= (sum-triple board triple) target-sum)
                  (diagonal-p triple)
                  (not (human-in-middle-p board))
                  (side-empty-p board)))
         *triples*)")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "Then use"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "lispyville-slurp")
                                                                      "on the three ending parentheses of the"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "let")
                                                                      "form to complete the new form.")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "After adding an"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "if")
                                                                      "form, we need to make this a function, so we can write the function definition above the entire"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "let")
                                                                      "form:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
                                                                      (pre
                                                                        (code :class "almighty-src almighty-src-lisp"
                                                                          "(defun detect-squeeze (board target-sum))
(let ((squeeze-p
        (find-if #'(lambda (triple)
                     (and (= (sum-triple board triple) target-sum)
                          (diagonal-p triple)
                          (not (human-in-middle-p board))
                          (side-empty-p board)))
                 *triples*)))
  (if squeeze-p
      (find-empty-position board *sides*)))")))
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "And then just slurp up the entire"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "let")
                                                                      "into the"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "defun")
                                                                      "form.")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "Again, you"
                                                                      (i
                                                                        "could")
                                                                      "just"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "kill")
                                                                      "and"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "paste")
                                                                      "the forms around, but killing can sometimes be dangerous (if you kill a word using"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "M-backspace")
                                                                      ", you've just replaced your function in the kill-ring). It's nicer to simply keep the code on the screen and using slurp to do what you want.")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "The reverse of"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "slurp")
                                                                      "is"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "barf")
                                                                      ", bound to"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "<")
                                                                      "in Doom Emacs"
                                                                      (code
                                                                        "lispyville-mode")
                                                                      ". I don't find it nearly as useful as slurping, but maybe you can find a use for it."))
                                                                  (article :class "almighty-section"
                                                                    (h3 :id "dragging-forms-forward-backward" :class "almighty-section-title"
                                                                      "Dragging forms forward/backward")
                                                                    (p :class "almighty-book-paragraph"
                                                                      "Another operation you'll probably want to do a lot is move forms around. For example, maybe you wrote this:")
                                                                    (figure :class "almighty-code-block"
